    <h1 class="blog-heading">
      LCOY Nepal 2025: Everything You Need to Know and How to Be Part of It
    </h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      If you've heard about LCOY Nepal 2025 and wondered what it is, how it
      works, and why it matters, you're in the right place. In this blog, we'll
      break down everything you need to know about LCOY and hopefully encourage
      your participation regardless of your knowledge level (because that's
      important!).
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="blog-content">
    <h2 class="blog-subheading">What is LCOY?</h2>
    <p>
      LCOY stands for Local Conference of Youth. It is a national-level climate
      conference officially endorsed by YOUNGO, the children and youth
      constituency of the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change
      (UNFCCC).
    </p>

    <p>
      If you're new to climate change and these terms feel unfamiliar, that's
      completely okay. Everyone starts somewhere and LCOY could be your very
      first step into the climate movement. Let's take a step back to understand
      the basics.
    </p>
    <p>
      The UNFCCC is an international treaty adopted in 1992 at the Earth Summit
      in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil. It provides the foundational framework for
      global action on climate change. The treaty came into force in 1994 and
      now has 198 member countries, making it almost universally adopted. To
      manage its processes, the UNFCCC Secretariat was established, which
      organizes the annual COPs (Conferences of the Parties) and supports
      countries in implementing the treaty.
    </p>

    <p>
      YOUNGO is the official children and youth constituency of the UNFCCC. Its
      mission is to empower young people, build their capacity, and ensure their
      voices are heard in climate decision-making at all levels. The Local
      Conference of Youth (LCOY) is one of YOUNGO's most important mechanisms
      for achieving this.
    </p>

    <h2 class="blog-subheading">Why is LCOY Important?</h2>
    <p>
      LCOY is a structured platform for young people to engage in climate
      dialogue, policy, and action.
    </p>
    <ul class="lcoy-importance">
      <li>
        Youth across the country gather to learn, discuss, and collaborate.
      </li>
      <li>
        The outcome is a National Youth Declaration, a document with
        recommendations, policy demands, and action priorities from young
        people.
      </li>
      <li>
        This declaration is presented to the government to highlight what
        Nepalese youth expect in terms of climate action and policies.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      But it doesn't stop there. The inputs from LCOY Nepal are carried forward
      to the Regional Conference of Youth (RCOY), where they are combined with
      youth perspectives from neighboring countries. From there, the outcomes
      move on to the Global Conference of Youth (COY), which takes place right
      before the annual COP (UN Climate Change Conference).
    </p>

    <p>
      This means the ideas and solutions you share in Nepal can travel all the
      way from local to global, influencing the discussions world leaders have
      at COP.
    </p>

    <p>This year marks the <strong>sixth edition of LCOY Nepal</strong>.</p>

