    <h2 class="blog-subheading">Nepal's Journey with LCOY</h2>
    <ul class="history-list">
      <li>
        <strong>2020 (Virtual):</strong> The first-ever LCOY Nepal (Nov 21–22), organized
        by Climates Nepal and Youth Thinkers' Society Chitwan, held online due to
        COVID-19.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2021 (Virtual):</strong> Organized by CliMates Nepal, NYCA, and Youth
        Thinkers' Society Chitwan (Oct 8–9).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2022 (Virtual):</strong> Hosted by Sustainability Week Kathmandu
        and NYCA (Oct 28–29).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2023 (In-person):</strong> The first physical LCOY (Sept 15–16),
        led by PowerShift Nepal with co-organizers including Sustainability Week
        Kathmandu, Thought for Food, Harin Nepal, International Forestry Students'
        Association, Female Foresters Nepal, Youth Action for Sustainable and Eco
        Nepal, Climates Nepal, Pravaha Collective, and Eco Network.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2024 (In-person):</strong> Organized by Youth Action for Sustainable
        and Eco Nepal and Sustainability Week Kathmandu (Aug 3–4).
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="blog-subheading">Why Should You Participate?</h2>
    <p>
      One of the best things about LCOY is that it is open to everyone from
      experienced climate activists to those just beginning their journey. You
      don't need to be an expert in climate science or policy to join.
    </p>
    <ul class="highlight-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Learn as You Go:</strong> LCOY is designed to grow your knowledge.
        You'll learn about climate basics, local solutions, and even how global negotiations
        work.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Your Voice Matters:</strong> Climate change affects everyone. Your
        ideas and experiences are valuable, and LCOY is where they are recognized.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Connect and Network:</strong> Meet like-minded peers, local leaders,
        and organizations. Many collaborations, friendships, and projects start at
        LCOY.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Be Part of a Global Movement:</strong> Your input doesn't stop at
        LCOY. It contributes to national, regional, and global youth statements that
        are presented to world leaders at UN climate negotiations.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Empowerment and Action:</strong> You'll leave not just informed,
        but also inspired and equipped to act, whether in your community or on a
        larger scale.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Don't hold back because you feel you <strong>"don't know enough."</strong>
      LCOY is the place to learn, grow, and shape the climate conversation alongside
      other youth.
    </p>

    <h2 class="blog-subheading">Our Story Began at LCOY Nepal 2023</h2>
    <p>
      Two years ago, our founder Bibek almost skipped LCOY. Coming from a tech
      background, he thought climate conferences weren't for him. At the last
      moment, he applied and it changed everything.
    </p>
    <p>
      He was one of only a few computer science participants, and he left LCOY
      shocked, inspired, and empowered to do something meaningful. The lack of
      accessible digital climate resources later pushed him to start building
      Nepal Climate Hub.
    </p>
    <blockquote>
      "LCOY changed everything. My career choice, my goals, and my outlook. LCOY
      is where you meet enthusiastic minds across disciplines. Don't wait until
      you <strong>'know enough.'</strong> Sometimes, taking the first step is all
      it takes." – Bibek
    </blockquote>

    <p>
      Today, Nepal Climate Hub stands as a nonprofit with a multidisciplinary
      team of 16 from all seven provinces and beyond (USA, Canada, Germany, and
      Scotland). Our Executive Director, Monica, was part of the organizing team
      for the first LCOY Nepal in 2020. Our Digital Community Manager, Gayatri,
      volunteered at LCOY 2024.
    </p>

    <p>
      We are committed to bringing youth from diverse fields: engineering,
      technology, health, law, economics, and beyond into the climate space. We
      believe in more inclusive conversations, more collaboration, and more
      innovation.
    </p>

    <p>
      Our simple goal: to make the climate journey easier for newcomers by
      curating and sharing beginner friendly resources. We are building an
      inclusive digital space for youth of Nepal to engage in conversation,
      share their expertise and collaborate to amplify the larger change in
      Nepalese climate movement.
    </p>

    <p class="closing">
      We look forward to seeing you at LCOY Nepal 2025. Join us, share your
      voice, and be part of the movement shaping our collective future.
    </p>

